{{nihongo|'''Lady Rokujō'''|六条御息所|Rokujō no Miyasundokoro}} is a fictional character in ''[[The Tale of Genji]]'' (''Genji Monogatari''). She is the widow of Prince Zembo and a longtime mistress of [[Hikaru Genji|Genji]]. She is named after her residence, which was located on the Sixth Street (''Rokujō'') of the capital city [[Heian-kyō]]. She has great pride, and her jealousy is so strong that subconsciously her ''[[ikiryō]]'' (wandering spirit) kills Yugao and [[Aoi no Ue|Lady Aoi]], and attacks [[Murasaki]].
[[File:Hokusai_Aoinoue.jpg|right|thumb|Lady Rokujo depicted as an ''ikiryō'' in the work titled {{nihongo|''[[Aoi no Ue]]''|葵上}} from the ''[[Hokusai Manga]]'' by [[Katsushika Hokusai]].]]

Lady Rokujō is the mother of Akikonomu, and travels with her when Akikonomu becomes the [[Ise Grand Shrine|Ise]] Priestess. After their return to the capital, when she is dying, Lady Rokujō entrusts Genji with guardianship of her daughter (chapter 14).  

